    \begin {tikzcd}
      D(Fc, Fc)\ar [r, leftrightarrow]\ar [d, "f_*"'] & C(c, GFc)\ar [d, "Gf_*"] \\
      D(Fc, d)\ar [r, leftrightarrow] & C(c, Gd)\makebox [0pt][l]{.}
    \end {tikzcd}


 Tracking 1_{Fc} along the top-right path, and recalling that \eta _c is
  defined as the transpose of 1_{Fc}, we get Gf\eta _c. Tracking it along
  the bottom-right path, we get the transpose of f. The formula for
  g^\sharp  follows similarly.

